         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">27/5/87. ¶  ¶ Reflecting on what you said, dear Mr Thomas, I deem it best to  ¶ speak ¶  in first instance to the Undersecretary, so that I may make no mistake in taking action regarding the distribut...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.05.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Ebenezer Thomas</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">P87/1748, unit 107, VPRS 1163/P1 inward correspondence files, VA 672 Premier's Office, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>27/5/87.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Reflecting on what you said, dear Mr Thomas, I deem it best to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">speak</hi>
               </seg> in first instance to the Undersecretary, so that I may make no mistake in taking action regarding the distribution of my works through the colony. Have you any means, to ascertain, how many free libraries and mechanic Institutes exist in [the]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition</seg> — MS obscured by binding. <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">well, obscured on p/c — can easily be checked on MS.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Colony? If you would let me know, it would be a help to me. As regards the […]plication<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">MS obscured by binding.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> from the Church of England Grammar school I may say that I never go there, and do not even know Mr Thomson by sight. Should at any time foreign science-institutions again apply to the hon. the Premier for any works issued in this colony, (though I shall <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> induce them to take that course) I would respectfully suggest, that they be requested to make a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">return</hi>
               </seg>-<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sending</hi>
               </seg> to the Melb. public Library; — and I feel sure, it will be done in the most compolitan<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">sic. — cosmopolitan? compliant?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> spirit. The principle […]<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">MS obscured by binding. ', for'? ', of'?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">my</hi>
               </seg> initiati[ng]<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">MS obscured by binding.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> a system of distribution of my [science] works <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">beyond interchanges</hi>
               </seg> comes upon me as an entirely <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new</hi>
               </seg> one; so I have to plead excuse for my unintentional shortcoming.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Perhaps you or some friend or your can use the byefollowing tickets</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">[…]<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">several words along margin obscured in p/c — to clarify sentence order.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> arise "select plants," as the sale of the last fully covered the cost.</p>
         </div>
